list.name: Default
list.comment: welp, now im in a new pickle where you SHOULD be running your socket.io/websocket server on the same port. I cant seem to handle the CORS issue. I cant get a connection from the port 3000 frontend to the port 3100 webserver running socket.io. Going to table this for now.

task.summary:
Working towards a better webapp template. Changed the server/app/index system.
new app file to manage the entire web app, services,databases and any other important app structure. new server file, this handles everything for actaually getting the webserver running. app ends up being an instance of the server and allows you to pile on top of it.
Soon a nice barebones skeleton will exist that can be employed to get webapp dev started sooner. This is a major update from my old skeletion that was about 2 years behind in tech.

Comming from an older version of hapi, I discoverd you can no longer use connections to manage multiple connections.
Instead you must now run multiple servers. So I setup app to host and manage multiple servers to allow for running of the API and any additional servers/services you need on another port.
Still trying to get socket.io up and running.
